			[ Release notes ]



Previous version: 1.75		(07/08/2004)
Current version:  1.79		(20/08/2004)

SubVersion (CVS) revision: $Id$

TiEmu is available for 2 platforms:
Linux (GTK), Windows (GTK).

If you have a SilverLink cable (TI-GRAPH LINK USB), you will need to retrieve
a Linux/Win32/Mac OS-X driver on the Linux Programmer Group at 
<http://lpg.ticalc.org/prj_usb>.

For the other link cables, no driver is needed because it's provided.


New capabilities:
-----------------

	- added refresh button in the mem window	
	- use Lionel's ROM call list (but can use TIGCC os.h file, too)
	- check for image at startup and can select it
	- accept ExtendeD's V200 ROM (patched)
	- can load keymap (PC to TI keyboard translation) from file


Improvements:
-------------

	- update registers when modifying the supervisor bit
	- minimizing/maximizing of windows improved
	- step over fixed again
	- FLINE > 5 was mis-disassembled
	- code window: don't reload source when setting a bkpt
	- code window: show PC in the middle of the window and leave 3 isntructions at bottom
	- changed keyboard mapping to pure VTi mapping
	- LCD background is less dark than before
	- mem window: refresh when scrolling up/down
		

Bug fixes:
----------

	- few bugs fixes

To do:
------

	- implement the Protection
	- implement the RTC introduced with AMS 2.09

	
